{"article_id":"QtedQHVsn1WEZt9q","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Trying to strike a balance between the government ' s surveillance policies and the public ' s civil liberties ,","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"President Obama announced a series of steps Friday","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"that would end the National Security Agency ' s ability","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"to store phone data","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"collected from millions of Americans .","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"However , Obama ,","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"speaking at the Justice Department ,","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"did not say","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"the program would end","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"-- only that the information","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"collected","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"would no longer be held by the NSA .","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"He also announced tighter restrictions on spying on international leaders .","depth":4},{"id":13,"text":"`` America ' s capabilities are unique , \"","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"Obama said during the nearly 45-minute speech .","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"\" That places a special obligation on us","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"to ask tough questions","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"about what we should do . ''","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"Obama did not offer his own plan","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"for where the NSA phone records should be moved","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"and said","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"instead he would call on the attorney general and members of the intelligence community to recommend a transfer point by March 28","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"- when the collection program comes up for reauthorization .","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"The president ' s directive also requires intelligence agencies to obtain approval from a FISA court","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"- a secret U.S. court","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"that governs surveillance of terrorist and foreign espionage targets -","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"before accessing the records .","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"Obama ' s directive follows the disclosure of the spy agency ' s surveillance practices by former NSA contractor-turned-leaker Edward Snowden .","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"\" While I am encouraged","depth":6},{"id":29,"text":"the president is addressing the NSA spying program","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"because of pressure from Congress and the American people ,","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"I disappointed in the details , \"","depth":5},{"id":32,"text":"Sen. Rand Paul , R-KY , said in a written statement .","depth":4},{"id":33,"text":"Nevada Republican Sen. Dean Heller says","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"significant policy questions still remain .","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"\" I have concerns","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"that requiring private companies to shoulder the burden for the NSA could simply shift privacy intrusions from the federal government to private companies , \"","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"he said .","depth":6},{"id":38,"text":"\" Further discussions are needed","depth":5},{"id":39,"text":"in order to achieve a workable solution","depth":6},{"id":40,"text":"that protects Americans ' Fourth Amendment rights . \"","depth":6},{"id":41,"text":"Civil libertarians said","depth":4},{"id":42,"text":"Obama did not go far enough","depth":5},{"id":43,"text":"to protect privacy","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"and prevent abuse .","depth":6},{"id":45,"text":"Steven W. Hawkins , executive director of Amnesty International USA , said ,","depth":5},{"id":46,"text":"`` President Obama 's surveillance adjustments will be remembered as music on the Titanic","depth":6},{"id":47,"text":"unless his administration adopts deeper reforms . '' `` Shifting the storage of information does not address the fundamental problem :","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"the collection of mass personal data in the first place , ''","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"Hawkins said in a statement .","depth":4},{"id":50,"text":"There appeared to be some initial confusion about Congress ' role","depth":5},{"id":51,"text":"in authorizing any changes .","depth":5},{"id":52,"text":"An administration official said","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"Obama could codify the data transfer through an executive order ,","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"while some congressional aides said","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"legislation would be required .","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"Congress would have to approve a proposal from the president","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"that would establish a panel of outside attorneys","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"who would consult with the secretive Foreign Intelligence Surveillance Court on new legal issues","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"that arise .","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"The White House says","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"the panel would advocate for privacy and civil liberties","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"as the court weighed requests","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"for accessing the phone records .","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"Obama also announced tighter restrictions on spying on international leaders .","depth":5},{"id":65,"text":"\" The heads of state and government","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"with whom we work closely ,","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"and on whose cooperation we depend ,","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"should feel confident","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"that we are treating them as real partners , \"","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"Obama said .","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"\" The changes","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"I 've ordered","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"do just that . \"","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"Documents","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"released by Snowden","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"revealed","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"that the U.S. was monitoring the communications of several foreign leaders ,","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"including German Chancellor Angela Merkel .","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"The revelations outraged Merkel as well as other leaders ,","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"and U.S. officials say","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"the disclosures have damaged Obama 's relations around the world .","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"Obama also said","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"the government could no longer request data beyond two people away from the terrorist target .","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"He also said","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"that ' dozens ' of foreign leaders would be safe from NSA surveillance techniques","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"but did not offer that protection to their advisers .","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"Sen. John McCain , R-Ariz. , said","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"he would introduce legislation","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"to create a special Senate committee","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"to examine the issues","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"and exercise congressional oversight .","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"`` Recent disclosures of these activities and practices have caused grave damage to the United States , ''","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"McCain said in a statement .","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"`` They have harmed our relations with friends and allies","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"and harmed our ability","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"to combat threats to the United States .","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"It is more important than ever for Congress to exercise effective oversight and ,","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"where necessary ,","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"to enact legislation","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"to address these issues","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"which are vital to American national security . ''","depth":12}],"relations":[{"parent":203,"left":142,"right":202,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":142,"left":129,"right":141,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":129,"left":114,"right":128,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":114,"left":113,"right":12,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":113,"left":106,"right":112,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{